HEADWORD: Impecunious
<hw>Im"pe*cu"ni*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>pecunia</ets> money: cf. F.
<ets>imp⟦eacute⟧cunieux</ets>.]</ety> <def>Not having money; habitually
without money; poor.</def>⟦br⟧
